title: Volatility Regains the Upper Hand as Trade Shift Rattles Markets
text:
A topsy-turvy week on Wall Street reaffirmed many tradersâ€™ hunch that stock-market volatility is back for the long haul, following an extended absence.
Major U.S. share-price indexes closed mixed Friday, shaking off an early plunge that took the Dow Jones Industrial Average down as many as 391 points. The Dow ended lower by 71 points and the Nasdaq and S&P 500 both rose.
